appears in first person view (the green bars when you pan the camera).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOpen an issue on github\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-30T05:19:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298149\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221687974006\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/28/2023 at 7:40 PM, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOpen an issue on github\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNvm, on a test lightly modded install it worked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo maybe it was a conflict before, or I messed up... ^^\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry for the disturbance !\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-30T11:34:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi again ^^\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027m having a weird one : same install, same save : two different craft files with external cmd chair : one is allowing to first person view on the chair, the other doesn\u0027t...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny idea why ?\u003Cbr\u003E\nAttached a zip with 3 craft files in question in case you want to test it (they\u0027re stock) \u003Cspan\u003E: \u0022test\u0022 and \u0022cesnuk 2\u0022 don\u0027t work, \u0022smal planuk 1\u0022 does.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/t0w2v8k68fkt1e8/craft%20files%20tests.zip?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/t0w2v8k68fkt1e8/craft files tests.zip?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nksp log :\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/14waidz2z44dicf/KSP.log?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/14waidz2z44dicf/KSP.log?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EThank you \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-30T11:34:41Z\u0022 title=\u002206/30/2023 11:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 30, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by kurgut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-30T12:07:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298628\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688124859\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntwo different craft files with external cmd chair : one is allowing to first person view on the chair, the other doesn\u0027t...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFound the answer ! When a craft has a probe core, it doesn\u0027t allow Kerbal view on command chair. And it\u0027s weird since I don\u0027t have probe control room.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you think it would be possible to change this behavior ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthx\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JonnyOThan","CreatedById":40902,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-30T12:40:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298636\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688126863\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFound the answer ! When a craft has a probe core, it doesn\u0027t allow Kerbal view on command chair. And it\u0027s weird since I don\u0027t have probe control room.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you think it would be possible to change this behavior ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthx\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow that\u0027s funny; I checked to see if you had PCR because there were some bugs with that before - but they should be fixed now, so maybe the answer is *installing* PCR.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-30T12:46:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298636\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688126863\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFound the answer ! When a craft has a probe core, it doesn\u0027t allow Kerbal view on command chair. And it\u0027s weird since I don\u0027t have probe control room.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you think it would be possible to change this behavior ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthx\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can take a look, thanks for identifying the problem\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688128810\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002240902\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JonnyOThan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, JonnyOThan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow that\u0027s funny; I checked to see if you had PCR because there were some bugs with that before - but they should be fixed now, so maybe the answer is *installing* PCR.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot really, not everyone nerds/wants PCR\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-30T12:57:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298650\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688129205\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmaybe the answer is *installing* PCR.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha, tried it \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E it didn\u0027t solve the issue. It would have the first time I\u0027d fix a mod\u0027s own issue, by installing a different mod \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298650\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688129205\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can take a look, thanks for identifying the problem\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you, also feature idea : it would be sweet to be able to switch between Kerbals view on command chairs, within a same vessel having multiple of them !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"theJesuit","CreatedById":122369,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-30T19:23:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298652\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688129863\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you, also feature idea : it would be sweet to be able to switch between Kerbals view on command chairs, within a same vessel having multiple of them !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile in IVA mode I think the stock game allows this by pressing V.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-30T20:22:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224298760\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221688153005\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122369\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022theJesuit\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n59 minutes ago, theJesuit said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile in IVA mode I think the stock game allows this by pressing V.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes but precisely this doesn\u0027t work for command chairs, since they\u0027re not an actual IVA. (just a kerbal sitting on part) : )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-30T20:23:15Z\u0022 title=\u002206/30/2023 08:23  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 30, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by kurgut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T07:31:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat does the\u00A0EVAKey do ? go EVA from the ext comand seat ? The key is marked as default in the settings, but what is the actual keyboard key for it ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso tought about an enhancement/QOL idea :\u00A0be able to open the Kerbal\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Part Action Window\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Part Action Window\u0022\u003EPAW\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E (via hotkey maybe?), so you don\u0027t need to constantly go to the external view to do science, or manage cargo, etc. With this you could all the time in 1st person view.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould this be achievable ?\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks ! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nEDIT : Wait sorry, I didn\u0027t read well the first post about PartComander... \u003Cspan\u003E: /\u003Cbr\u003E\nEDIT 2 : Well it also appears that if you look down you can right on the Kebal\u0027s body and open the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Part Action Window\u0022\u003EPAW\u003C/abbr\u003E..\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nSorry again, I\u0027ll let this post here just for reference for other people like me that don\u0027t read carefully the first post ^^\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-22T08:03:43Z\u0022 title=\u002212/22/2023 08:03  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 22\u0022\u003EDecember 22, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by kurgut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T08:21:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E Also, I started developping an IVA mod, that adds an interactive ASET IVA for the stock ext cmd seat.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nI first attached an internal to the part, and looked through the eyes, but the props didn\u0027t render, unless I turned IVA overlay ON. Also none of the props were producing sound, since there is no \u0022Active IVA Kerbal\u0022 indeed.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo I did find a way around it : create a variant of the chair, remove the kerbalseat module, and add a command module, to make it behave like a pod, add hatches modules, built an IVA around it, and it works ( see the WIP thread below) !\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut in the future, maybe it would be nice to have this working with TTE ? To avoid adding a new part ? What is the camera method you\u0027re using right now ? I\u0027d guess it\u0027s not an internalseat,\u00A0 but just the same as when being in EVA mode ? Since the Kerbal is technically in EVA mode when on the seat...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5497629847\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/221695-wip-aset-iva-for-the-eternal-command-seat/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:192px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks again !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-22T08:22:34Z\u0022 title=\u002212/22/2023 08:22  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 22\u0022\u003EDecember 22, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by kurgut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JonnyOThan","CreatedById":40902,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T13:11:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224350297\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703233301\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat is the camera method you\u0027re using right now ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI changed it to use the InternalCamera in order to fix clipping and z-fighting issues, mainly in VR.\u00A0 The helmet and body are changed to the IVA layers so that they draw on top of everything else.\u00A0 I think TTE would need to be adjusted to spawn the IVA for external command chairs if it exists (kind of like how PCR does the same for probe cores).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe behavior you reported about your mod when using the IVA overlay is interesting; I wonder if the game is force-rendering the internal camera again on top of the scene.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe audio issue probably just means that the audio listener on the internal camera is disabled or not set up correctly....or maybe RPM is trying to be smart and optimized when you\u0027re not actually in IVA mode.\u00A0 Needs investigating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"minerbat","CreatedById":201971,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-11T10:51:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsuggestion: could swimming be improved? right now when you swim with a helmet on the camera goes through the back of the helmet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OKBTrurl","CreatedById":233824,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-07-06T15:52:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you disable external view? Also, how do you repack personal parachutes and stuff without it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-07-06T15:53:02Z\u0022 title=\u002207/06/2024 03:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Jul 6\u0022\u003EJuly 6\u003C/time\u003E by OKBTrurl\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EClarification\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SheepDog2142","CreatedById":128819,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-07-13T03:33:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223279829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166786\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517153729\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/28/2018 at 9:35 AM, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis IS working, but I can see your confusion.\u00A0 I\u0027ve updated the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E with some more instructions regarding the keys used to control the Kerbal during EVA.\u00A0 Look at the new Settings page I just added for the option to force the IVA before launch.\u00A0 Note that you were always able to do IVA manually, this just forces it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you try hitting the \u0022C\u0022 key to get into IVA mode?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew Release, 2.0.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nMoved some options into setting screen:\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nforceEVA\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nshowSightAngle\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nforceIVA\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\ndisableMapView\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nMoved key options to the ThroughTheEyes/PluginData directory\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdded option to force IVA before launch\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you add the above options back to the config. In the settings menu they dont work with Luna Multiplayer as it wont save settings. However if they are in the config they will still work since its client side.\u00A0 I know its a conflict with another mod but it would be nice to be able to adjust them in both.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0forceEVA\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0showSightAngle\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0forceIVA\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0disableMapView\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"}]}